        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Zend_Dojo_Form_Decorator_DijitElement always sets the \"required\" attribute since issue #7660:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n$dijitParams['required'] = $element->isRequired();\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThis causes invalid browser behavior as the HTML5 \"required\" attribute (http:\/\/www.w3schools.com\/html5\/html5_form_attributes.asp) defines an element as required if the attribute is present, regardless of the attribute value. So e.g. Firefox 5 displays \"Fill out this element\" on hover.\r\n\r\nRendering a non-required Zend_Form_Element_Text in an dojo-enabled (programmatic mode) form results in following html:\r\n{code:html}\r\n<input type=\"text\" required=\"\" value=\"\" id=\"type\" name=\"type\" \/>\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nAdditionally: Shouldn't the attribute be rendered as required=\"false\" \/ required=\"true\" as other boolean attributes are rendered in Zend_Dojo_ and as it was before the changes of #7760?\r\n\r\nRequired elements render with \"1\" as attribute value instead of \"true\":\r\n{code:html}\r\n<input type=\"text\" required=\"1\" value=\"\" id=\"power_output\" name=\"power_output\" \/>\r\n{code}"
        },
